1383–1428","1400–Female":"1400–Deceased","1437":"1437","1434":"1434","1367":"1367","1400":"1400","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","27 October 1434":"27 October 1434","1428":"1428","Bardwell, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bardwell, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Isle of Man":"Isle of Man","Long Melford, Suffolk, England":"Long Melford, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Pakenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pakenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Saxon Parva, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pakenham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Pakenham (Suffolk). The placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Pacca</i> (genitive <i>Paccan</i>) + <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’.","History: A family of this name has been established in Westmeath, Ireland, since the 16th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret de Pakenham was born in 1367, in Pakenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with William de Berdewell. She died in 1437, in Bardwell, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1367–1437":"1367–1437","1361–1434":"1361–1434","1383–1428":"1383–1428","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1437":"1437","1434":"1434","1367":"1367","1400":"1400","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","27 October 1434":"27. oktoober 1434","1428":"1428","Bardwell, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bardwell, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Isle of Man":"Mani saar","Long Melford, Suffolk, England":"Long Melford, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Pakenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pakenham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Saxon Parva, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1367–1437":"1367–1437","1361–1434":"1361–1434","1383–1428":"1383–1428","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1437":"1437","1434":"1434","1367":"1367","1400":"1400","1383":"1383","1361":"1361","27 October 1434":"27. lokakuuta 1434","1428":"1428","Bardwell, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Bardwell, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Isle of Man":"Mansaari","Long Melford, Suffolk, England":"Long Melford, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Pakenham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Pakenham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Saxon Parva, Suffolk, England